# GitHub Copilot operating instructions — {{PROJECT_NAME}} brain

Canonical operating contract: `AGENTS.md`.
These instructions keep lane behavior aligned with Brain Factory standards.

## SYNC-LATEST-FIRST STANDARD (required)

- Sync to latest online default branch before decisions, session creation, or
  changes (`git fetch`; base on `origin/<default>`).
- Start each new work session from an up-to-date default branch.
- Re-sync lane/app repos before touching them directly.
- Verify PR mergeability against current online default branch before merge.
- On session start/rehydration, refresh managed lanes before acting/reporting.

## CLEANUP-NO-STALE-STATE STANDARD (required)

- Cleanup triad: remote **BRANCH**, local **WORKTREE**, owning **SESSION**.
- Tear down the full triad together after merge.
- Session definition (GitHub Copilot): the app/project session and its worktree.
- Apply the same no-loss gate before deleting branch/worktree/session; preserve
  or escalate if unique unmerged content exists.
- Run periodic stale-state audits and flag merged-but-undeleted branches,
  branches with no open PR, orphaned worktrees, and orphaned sessions.
- Target one active worktree and one active session per active task.

## CONTINUITY-CAPTURE / BRAIN-MEMORY WRITEBACK STANDARD (required)

- For work executed in any lane repo (product/runtime or governance), the lane
  brain records WHAT, WHY, WHERE (repo + PR/commit), and OUTCOME.
- Orchestrator actions write back to continuity ledger + master session index
  after directing/executing lane work.
- A lane change without brain continuity entry is a defect (memory loss).
- Capture in-progress at start/PR open and finalize on merge.
- Cross-link product/runtime PR and brain continuity entry where practical.
- No-loss continuity invariant: memory spans all lane repos, not only governance.
